  "source_notes": {
    "fa_sliding_off": "FA_SLIDING=1 flips [0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0] target layers in default (0 => the FA2 sliding-window swap is INERT on this build); FA_SLIDING=0 tokens are 1.0 identical to default => the toggle changes nothing, so its -0.02% TPS delta is a no-op artifact, not a kernel-swap cost.",
    "atomic_on": "VLLM_MARLIN_USE_ATOMIC_ADD=1 is NOT inert (single changed env var; fa_flips/splitkv match default): tokens are only 0.1116 identical to default (it shifts the verify-GEMM numerics) AND it fails the clean bit-exactness the default shows -- a single first-reload OUTLIER: 2 distinct outputs over 7 reloads with the largest cluster 6/7 mutually byte-identical -- consistent with a one-time autotune/warm-up of the newly-enabled atomic-add kernel path, NOT per-token stochastic noise (mean byte-identical 0.8214, official xcheck DIVERGENT, divergence onset median 155/512). The deployed default keeps atomic-add OFF and is bit-exact across ALL reloads incl. the first, so keeping it off is load-bearing. NB: the 'Marlin bf16 before SM90' warning was NOT seen in logs, so warning-absence is not proof the path is gated off -- the measured token change proves it engaged.",
    "splitkv_off": "SPLITKV_VERIFY genuinely engages in default ([5, 5, 5, 5, 5, 5, 5] verify redirects/reload, log-capped at 5); disabling it leaves tokens 0.0859 identical to default and default stays self-identical (1.0) => the #43 3D split-KV reduction order is run-to-run stable."
  },
